01:20.289 --> 01:22.972
The Democratic Republic of Congo
is the scene of the worst

01:23.072 --> 01:26.830
humanitarian crisis in the world
according to the United Nations.

01:27.530 --> 01:30.761
<i>In what has been described
as the world's deadliest conflict</i>

01:30.861 --> 01:34.338
<i>since World War II,
millions of people have been killed.</i>

01:35.304 --> 01:39.567
<i>Massacres and rape,
routinely used as weapons of war,</i>

01:39.667 --> 01:43.746
<i>have forced hundreds of thousands
of people to flee their homes.</i>

01:43.846 --> 01:48.909
<i>For years, the United Nations
and non-governmental organizations, NGOs,</i>

01:49.009 --> 01:53.814
<i>have been providing humanitarian relief
in an increasingly unstable situation,</i>

01:53.914 --> 01:57.331
<i>often requiring the presence
of private security contractors</i>

01:57.431 --> 01:59.920
<i>to ensure aid workers' safety.</i>

02:00.020 --> 02:03.132
<i>The conflict is fuelled
by the country's vast mineral wealth,</i>

02:03.232 --> 02:06.954
<i>with all sides suspected
of deliberately prolonging the violence</i>

02:07.428 --> 02:10.823
<i>to plunder natural resources
such as gold, diamonds,</i>

02:10.923 --> 02:14.744
<i>copper, coltan,
and other high-value minerals</i>

02:14.844 --> 02:18.273
<i>to meet the growing demand
of the Western world.</i>

02:19.949 --> 02:24.086
<i>Despite calls for a ceasefire
and the presence of UN peacekeepers,</i>

02:24.186 --> 02:28.617
<i>a deteriorating humanitarian situation
of poverty and corruption</i>

02:28.758 --> 02:35.289
<i>jeopardize hopes of a lasting peace
and reconstruction of the shattered nation.</i>

03:01.640 --> 03:02.900
Jimmy!

03:03.000 --> 03:04.919
- Hey.
- What are you drinking?

03:05.019 --> 03:07.521
Oh, you guys look pretty tonight,
but I got my gal over here.

03:07.621 --> 03:10.883
- I'll buy you one.
- Roger that, Jim.

03:10.983 --> 03:12.401
- Hey, chief.
- Hey, what's happening?

03:12.501 --> 03:14.403
- We're up to here in mud out there.
- Jesus.

03:14.503 --> 03:17.407
- So I shut down the site for tonight.
- Will it be ready?

03:17.507 --> 03:21.477
There are not enough of us.
We have to meet the new Minister of Health.

03:21.577 --> 03:25.222
We need his support
to train medical staff locally.

03:25.322 --> 03:27.233
I'll get a face-to-face meeting
and we'll go together.

03:27.333 --> 03:28.259
Okay.

03:28.359 --> 03:30.412
- I'll email him now.
- Thank you. Hey.

03:32.396 --> 03:33.889
- How are you?
- Good.

03:33.989 --> 03:35.650
- Hey. How are you?
- What's up?

03:35.750 --> 03:39.094
- Where am I? Where do you want me?
- Here. No.

03:39.194 --> 03:41.664
What are you having, Jim?

03:41.764 --> 03:44.108
I'll have a pretty little thing
just like Annie's got here.

03:44.208 --> 03:46.586
- A blue one.
- A blue one, yeah.

03:50.222 --> 03:54.310
- Was there anything else, Annie?
- Yes, there was.

03:54.410 --> 03:58.798
We also need to coordinate with local NGOs
to distribute condoms outside the clinics...

03:58.898 --> 04:02.009
Oh, man. Don't talk to me
about condom distribution.

04:02.109 --> 04:04.420
It's like rape promotion
in these villages.

04:04.520 --> 04:06.881
You might as well
hand them out to the wild dogs.

04:06.981 --> 04:10.117
And a great humanitarian, Mr. Terry Cox.

04:10.217 --> 04:12.561
Wait a minute. How long
we been friends? Twenty years?

04:12.661 --> 04:15.214
I think that's the first time
I've ever heard you call me a humanitarian.

04:15.314 --> 04:17.116
<i>Our main story from Africa,</i>

04:17.216 --> 04:19.652
<i>where the Minister of Mining
and Natural Resources</i>

04:19.752 --> 04:23.139
<i>of the Democratic Republic of Congo
has triggered a burst of reactions</i>

04:23.239 --> 04:25.718
<i>from the international community
this afternoon</i>

04:25.818 --> 04:27.585
<i>by announcing the decision to cancel</i>

04:27.685 --> 04:31.907
<i>and renegotiate all pre-existing contracts
with foreign mining companies.</i>

04:32.206 --> 04:34.675
<i>With growing evidence
of political corruption,</i>

04:34.775 --> 04:38.354
<i>there are questions regarding
the motivations behind this decision,</i>

04:38.454 --> 04:40.265
<i>but the minister
advocates the restricted...</i>

05:01.694 --> 05:03.612
Good morning, honey.

05:03.712 --> 05:07.041
- I've gotta go to work.
- Okey-dokey.

05:07.566 --> 05:10.036
Really. We are short on staff.

05:10.136 --> 05:11.679
- I have to.
- Okay, sweetheart.

05:11.779 --> 05:15.709
- You have a good day at work.
- Let me go.

05:32.992 --> 05:36.628
- Don't you have to go to work, too?
- I think I got a couple of hours.

05:36.728 --> 05:39.899
I gotta grab some stuff from my place,
and then get out to the site.

05:39.999 --> 05:41.426
What are you doing over there?

05:42.209 --> 05:45.471
Aren't you guys here to work for us?
To protect us?

05:45.571 --> 05:49.325
I am your 24-hour personal bodyguard.

05:49.425 --> 05:52.871
I'm putting my meanest guys
on the clinic tonight. You'll be safe.

05:55.514 --> 05:57.625
Will you work late?

05:57.725 --> 05:59.953
I'm hoping not.

06:01.353 --> 06:03.381
I'll see you later.

06:07.359 --> 06:08.787
See you later, Jim.

06:16.077 --> 06:19.147
<i>How we doing on
the perimeter-fence check? Over.</i>

06:19.538 --> 06:21.107
<i>Perimeter checked and secured.</i>

06:21.207 --> 06:25.444
<i>This security detail's getting boring.
I can't wait to see some real action.</i>

06:25.544 --> 06:27.420
<i>It's crazy hot out here tonight.</i>

06:27.520 --> 06:30.482
<i>I've made sure that every checkpoint
is resupplied with fresh water.</i>

06:30.582 --> 06:32.785
Roger that. I don't know about you,

06:32.885 --> 06:36.197
<i>but I find it harder and harder
to focus out here in this heat.</i>

06:36.297 --> 06:38.933
I've been letting the dehydration
get to my memory so much,

06:39.033 --> 06:41.777
<i>I'm having to start writing shit down
just to remember to take a piss.</i>

06:41.877 --> 06:46.550
I was video-documenting on my cell phone
earlier, like a goddamn wazoo.

06:47.149 --> 06:49.327
Action at the gate. Sitrep.

06:49.427 --> 06:51.772
<i>Roger. Two NGO vehicles on site.</i>

06:52.538 --> 06:55.232
<i>Seems to be Felix's escort.</i>

07:01.230 --> 07:05.469
<i>Felix and Cox jabbering. What do you figure
that's all about at 2200 hours?</i>

07:05.968 --> 07:10.573
- On my mark, switch to all freq 4.
- <i>Roger. Switching now.</i>

07:11.090 --> 07:13.360
- <i>Reed, Jim. Check.</i>
- Lima Charlie to me.

07:14.885 --> 07:18.206
I got a feeling we're going operational.

07:48.361 --> 07:49.554
- Hey, Annie.
- Felix.

07:49.654 --> 07:53.500
- Hello. Is he gonna make it?
- Till the next time.

07:54.099 --> 07:55.493
- I need a break.
- Sure.

07:55.593 --> 08:00.206
We've had five of those
machete wounds today. We lost two.

08:00.306 --> 08:02.825
Another day in paradise.

08:02.925 --> 08:04.752
Did you get us a meeting
with the Minister of Health?

08:04.852 --> 08:07.079
Yeah. 9:00 tomorrow morning, you and I.

08:07.179 --> 08:10.650
- Happy?
- Did you go to the airstrip tonight?

08:10.858 --> 08:14.136
- Just for a few minutes. Administrative.
- Did you see Jim?

08:14.236 --> 08:16.305
I didn't speak to him.
I didn't wanna bother him.

08:16.405 --> 08:20.110
They've got a big job out there,
and I had a sense they'd go late.

08:21.827 --> 08:24.480
He's a lucky man, Jim Terrier.

08:24.580 --> 08:27.865
- He's a hard man.
- If only you could love a soft one.

08:33.706 --> 08:37.753
- Can I drive you home?
- Thanks, but I'll wait for Jim.

08:38.152 --> 08:39.370
Okay.

08:39.470 --> 08:42.398
There's plenty of work here
for me to pass the time.

08:42.498 --> 08:45.076
I only stopped by to ask you that.

09:01.367 --> 09:02.952
Hey, Jim. Document this.

09:03.052 --> 09:05.346
Oh, Reed! Watch where
you point that weapon, man.

09:05.446 --> 09:07.039
Have some barrel control, man.

09:07.139 --> 09:08.824
All right, mates,
here are your target packs.

09:08.924 --> 09:12.037
Drop that, Jimmy.
This is Operation Calvary.

09:12.536 --> 09:14.422
We insert as a team here,

09:14.522 --> 09:18.559
four degrees, 18 minutes south,
15 degrees, 18 minutes east.

09:18.659 --> 09:23.424
Reed, you are Sierra 1, and you'll be
positioned here, in a third-floor apartment.

09:23.524 --> 09:27.835
Two blocks down will be Bryson,
Sierra 2, and Jim, Sierra 3.

09:27.935 --> 09:32.210
You're the lucky one, Jim.
Double bedroom at the Grand Hotel.

09:34.751 --> 09:35.877
Reed, report.

09:35.977 --> 09:38.313
Tango 1 is completing
a three-car convoy.

09:38.612 --> 09:41.733
Fronting and backing vehicles
are low profile, soft skins.

09:42.232 --> 09:45.837
Target vehicle:
B7 armored white, Toyota Land Cruiser.

09:46.963 --> 09:50.021
The convoy will travel westbound
down the boulevard.

09:50.121 --> 09:54.987
He'll hit a natural choke point, giving us
three to five-second window of opportunity.

09:55.087 --> 09:57.999
Yeah. You guys are already zeroed
for ballistic advantage.

09:58.099 --> 10:01.452
Your drop cards are adjusted
to Kinshasa density altitude, right?

10:01.552 --> 10:02.853
- Roger that.
- Roger. Green light?

10:02.953 --> 10:05.706
Felix will give the green light
when he confirms the target is inbound.

10:05.806 --> 10:09.602
Felix will also designate
which of you shooters engages.

10:09.702 --> 10:11.763
- Any other questions?
- Extraction plan?

10:12.062 --> 10:15.809
Once the hit occurs, the shooter,
and the shooter only, is into the wind.

10:17.635 --> 10:21.180
- Off continent?
- Yeah. We have a plane on standby.

10:21.280 --> 10:23.657
That's how Felix wants it.

10:23.757 --> 10:26.689
Don't let the target escape the X.

11:37.898 --> 11:40.326
<i>Sierra 3, copy.</i>

11:40.451 --> 11:41.770
Sierra 3, Lima Charlie.

11:42.962 --> 11:45.215
<i>Nice night in Kinshasa, huh?</i>

11:51.036 --> 11:52.823
You are the designated trigger, Jim.

11:57.151 --> 12:00.663
I had a feeling. Roger that.

12:05.284 --> 12:07.996
- Hey.
- <i>I'm here.</i>

12:14.176 --> 12:16.709
Look out for her for me, will you?

12:17.505 --> 12:22.010
I will take care of Annie.
You have my word, Jim.

12:35.831 --> 12:38.459
<i>Calvary is confirmed.</i>

12:39.151 --> 12:42.822
<i>Stand by. Stand by.
Confirm Tango 1 on the move.</i>

12:42.922 --> 12:46.058
<i>Vehicle speed: 30 miles per hour.
Rear right passenger seat.</i>

12:46.158 --> 12:49.954
<i>Calvary is a go. Repeat.
Calvary is a go.</i>

13:00.314 --> 13:02.309
Stand by. Stand by. I have control.

13:24.113 --> 13:27.400
<i>Tango 1 down. Liftoff. Liftoff.</i>

13:40.755 --> 13:43.216
See you later, Annie.

13:47.078 --> 13:50.134
The latest reports
from the Democratic Republic of Congo,

13:50.234 --> 13:53.834
<i>where the unclaimed assassination
of the Minister of Mining</i>

13:53.934 --> 13:58.173
<i>has triggered violent confrontations
in the capital city of Kinshasa.</i>

13:58.889 --> 14:02.594
<i>Across the country, clashes between
government forces and rebels,</i>

14:02.893 --> 14:05.663
<i>along with indiscriminate raids
on civilian populations,</i>

14:05.763 --> 14:09.084
<i>have started again
with rising intensity.</i>

14:09.383 --> 14:13.496
<i>A country already crippled by corruption
in a decade of civil war</i>

14:13.596 --> 14:16.457
<i>descends even further into chaos.</i>

15:06.273 --> 15:07.892
<i>Bonjour.</i>

15:08.500 --> 15:10.207
<i>Bonjour.</i>

15:13.914 --> 15:15.400
Hey!

15:37.996 --> 15:39.857
Hey!

15:40.650 --> 15:43.252
Customs released the humanitarian
aid cargo yesterday,

15:43.352 --> 15:47.748
so we've just received this new shipment
of rice, canned food, and medical supplies.

15:47.848 --> 15:49.467
We need to extend our storage space

15:49.567 --> 15:51.620
and we're running a little short
on lumber, but it's not a problem.

15:51.819 --> 15:54.105
We've also received the water pumps
that Jim asked for,

15:54.205 --> 15:56.833
so he can now finish
setting up the water wells.

15:58.901 --> 16:01.679
Jim, you're up, but you know this meeting
is for department heads only.

16:01.779 --> 16:03.907
Oh. Forgive the liberty.
Eugene's my chainman.

16:04.731 --> 16:08.284
We are loading up on the remaining
pipe today, 150 feet of joint,

16:08.384 --> 16:11.864
push on, hit our mark on well bore
NLT this evening.

16:11.964 --> 16:14.792
As you were. No later than this evening.

16:14.892 --> 16:16.753
- We have CBM information?
- Eugene.

16:17.662 --> 16:20.439
Sitrep. Coal bed methane rating
is below standard

16:20.539 --> 16:23.693
and presents no risk of contamination
to the groundwater bed.

16:23.793 --> 16:25.679
But lots of clean water for my people.

16:25.978 --> 16:28.150
Thank you.

16:28.414 --> 16:31.376
I got a couple of teenagers back home
I'd like you to spend some time with.

16:31.476 --> 16:35.897
Jim has many qualities, but we still have
a security issue. Regarding surfing.

16:36.622 --> 16:38.891
Jim, come on. You've been here
for over a year now.

16:38.991 --> 16:41.445
You know security protocol
apply to all staff.

16:43.396 --> 16:47.659
Is that a new shirt?
Sorry. It's very pretty.

17:33.304 --> 17:36.291
- It's okay. It's okay.
- I'll pull it away.

17:42.054 --> 17:43.465
Okay, just...

18:26.139 --> 18:27.765
Jim!

18:41.989 --> 18:43.709
Eugene, stop.

20:06.031 --> 20:08.727
- Are there any more?
- No.

20:12.204 --> 20:15.933
Are you okay? Eugene, are you okay?

20:16.033 --> 20:17.302
- You sure?
- Yeah.

20:38.481 --> 20:42.357
Okay, Eugene, listen to me,
you did the right thing.

20:42.457 --> 20:46.330
You hear me? You did the right thing.
And now you're gonna do more, okay?

20:46.430 --> 20:48.941
Come on. Get all of our people back
to the compound.

20:49.041 --> 20:51.644
Tell Camille to lock down
all projects and all AOs.

20:51.744 --> 20:53.871
I'm gonna send a cab
back to the compound.

20:53.971 --> 20:57.233
Have security just throw my ruck
over the wall. Nobody goes outside.

20:57.333 --> 20:58.943
Then, tomorrow, when it's safe,

20:59.043 --> 21:01.112
have all the nationals reabsorb
into the community,

21:01.212 --> 21:03.615
go to emergency evac plan
for the expats.

21:03.856 --> 21:05.282
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

21:05.382 --> 21:06.851
- Are the keys in the Rover?
- Yeah. Sure.

21:06.951 --> 21:10.496
Okay. Give that to security.
Now can you do that?

21:10.596 --> 21:12.790
- I will take you to Kinshasa, Mr. Jim.
- No, no, no, Eugene.

21:12.890 --> 21:15.502
You've gotta do what I asked you to do
because you're the one who can do it.

21:15.701 --> 21:18.338
You understand? Okay.

21:18.737 --> 21:23.493
I've got a lot of respect for you, young man.
You saved my life. I'll never forget that.

22:07.653 --> 22:10.849
<i>Sierra 3, come in. Sierra 3.</i>

22:13.509 --> 22:16.245
<i>Don't let the target escape the X.</i>

22:22.818 --> 22:27.031
<i>Stand by. Stand by.
Confirm Tango 1 on the move.</i>

22:38.768 --> 22:40.363
<i>Calvary is a go.</i>

22:45.441 --> 22:49.963
<i>...and the crew, we'd like to welcome you
aboard this flight to London.</i>

24:28.377 --> 24:29.762
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

24:29.862 --> 24:31.948
- Hey. Jim Terrier.
- Terry.

24:33.466 --> 24:36.096
For fuck's sake. Oh, man.

24:36.196 --> 24:39.649
I heard you were living in London all
this time. You don't call, you don't write.

24:39.749 --> 24:42.525
- Yeah.
- Please, will you sit down?

24:42.625 --> 24:45.002
I'm surprised that they let you in,
looking like that.

24:45.102 --> 24:46.921
- Do you want a drink?
- No, thanks.

24:47.021 --> 24:50.892
Yeah, no, I was living in London
for several years

24:50.992 --> 24:54.621
after our escapade in Congo.

24:55.212 --> 24:58.373
Not a proud moment,
and I guess I felt awkward reaching out.

24:58.473 --> 25:02.244
Well, you always worried too much, Jim.
The past is the past, my friend.

25:02.344 --> 25:07.375
I see you lost the mustache. Looks good.
I never cared for the mustache on you.

25:08.834 --> 25:13.180
Boy, these are nice digs.
You've done well, huh?

25:13.280 --> 25:18.736
Me? Well, yeah. Company's expanded
since you retired, went multinational.

25:18.836 --> 25:22.899
Provides much more extensive services
now in machinery, weaponry, expertise.

25:22.999 --> 25:25.109
I don't know about you,
I just seem to travel all the time.

25:25.209 --> 25:29.605
Branches worldwide.
You see, no more Kevlar vests for me.

25:29.705 --> 25:33.326
I went from killer to cashier.
Don't tell anyone.

25:36.153 --> 25:38.513
You look worried, Jim. What is it?

25:38.989 --> 25:42.727
Terry, who all knew
about Project Calvary?

25:43.427 --> 25:47.340
- Why do you wanna dig up that history?
- I was in Congo for the last year.

25:47.440 --> 25:50.635
Yesterday, three indigs came after me,
specifically after me.

25:51.727 --> 25:54.307
Specifically after you?

25:57.842 --> 26:02.747
That's not good. Well, for all our sakes,
I hope you're wrong.

26:02.847 --> 26:06.308
Who knew about Calvary? You, me, Reed,
and Bryson. But we're all brothers.

26:06.408 --> 26:09.137
The clients knew, of course,
but who they were, I don't know.

26:09.237 --> 26:13.190
I mean, mining corporations,
politicians...

26:13.290 --> 26:16.427
That information was way above
my pay grade back then.

26:16.527 --> 26:20.072
Felix Marti was the only civilian
who knew about it.

26:20.172 --> 26:22.758
He was the only direct contact
with the clients.

26:22.858 --> 26:26.141
I think if your gut instinct is that
this trouble is related to Calvary,

26:26.241 --> 26:31.125
then we should both track down
Felix Marti, find out who's behind it.

26:31.225 --> 26:33.836
The last I heard,
he was back in Barcelona.

26:33.936 --> 26:36.019
I think I should track down
Reed and Bryson

26:36.119 --> 26:38.841
and give them the heads up.
I think they might be operating still.

26:38.941 --> 26:42.020
We should keep in contact about this.
How can I reach you?

26:42.219 --> 26:43.897
I'll call you.

26:44.196 --> 26:47.913
You keep your eyes open 'cause
they could be coming after you, too.

27:03.857 --> 27:05.444
<i>Terrier just walked out
of the company's building.</i>

27:10.389 --> 27:13.535
<i>Heading west towards the junction.
North side.</i>

27:14.818 --> 27:16.578
<i>Crossing the street now.</i>

27:18.089 --> 27:21.977
<i>Sunglasses, parka, camo backpack.
Oscar 1, he's coming your way.</i>

27:27.206 --> 27:31.670
<i>He's ex-Special Forces. Don't tail him
too close. He could spot you.</i>

27:44.716 --> 27:47.322
- <i>He's heading for the subway.</i>
- Stay with him?

27:47.422 --> 27:50.905
<i>Negative. Stand down.
We'll take it from here.</i>

28:06.470 --> 28:08.065
- Did you come alone?
- Well, what do you think?

28:08.664 --> 28:10.709
- How long have you known me?
- I mean, you're sure you weren't followed?

28:10.850 --> 28:13.536
After I received your message,
I caught two tubes,

28:13.636 --> 28:17.906
walked twice round Victoria Park,
like a fucking lunatic.

28:18.006 --> 28:20.193
What's going on?

28:21.585 --> 28:25.123
Jim, they're brain dead.
They only care about the match.

28:25.622 --> 28:29.134
Three pipe-hitters just tried
to take me down in Congo, Stan.

28:29.234 --> 28:31.462
Fuck me.

28:31.804 --> 28:33.305
What makes you think
they were after you?

28:33.405 --> 28:35.458
It's the Congo, for fuck's sake.
What do you expect?

28:35.558 --> 28:39.671
If we were to drop into Liberia tomorrow,
there'd be one or two feisty campers

28:39.812 --> 28:40.913
who'd wanna kick the shit
out of most white blokes.

28:41.013 --> 28:44.492
It wasn't regular army, Stanley,
it wasn't rebels, it wasn't FARDC.

28:45.284 --> 28:46.452
- All right.
- All right?

28:46.552 --> 28:48.438
Fucking cupcake.

28:51.039 --> 28:53.110
- You're paranoid?
- Yeah.

28:55.394 --> 28:59.582
Somebody wanted 50 ccs of me
for proof of kill. Is that paranoid?

28:59.682 --> 29:02.301
Whoever it is that sent those hitters,

29:02.401 --> 29:04.471
they've figured out by now
that I'm still alive.

29:04.970 --> 29:09.450
I need to find out who wants me dead
before they find me again.

29:10.910 --> 29:12.713
Well, Jim,

29:13.812 --> 29:16.507
I'll put you up for a job, right,
keep you off the grid.

29:16.607 --> 29:19.176
- It's black work, your type...
- No, I don't do that anymore.

