we'd like to share with him?

43:57.688 --> 43:59.558
- We have champagne.
- Felix, stop.

43:59.857 --> 44:05.063
Felix, what? Felix, what? Pretty soon,
we'll be saying, "Felix Junior, stop."

44:05.204 --> 44:06.494
Stop!

44:06.594 --> 44:08.846
What? What happened? What... Sorry.

44:08.946 --> 44:11.046
Am I missing anything?

44:11.368 --> 44:13.688
Why is everyone so tense? I mean...

44:13.838 --> 44:17.116
if you think of the coincidence
of all of this, you should not be tense.

44:17.216 --> 44:19.878
A dear and old friend arrives in town

44:20.019 --> 44:22.788
just as we are formalizing
the adoption of our first child.

44:22.888 --> 44:25.891
- I think it's a reason enough to...
- Stop.

44:25.991 --> 44:27.419
- Sit down.
- You're humiliating me.

44:27.560 --> 44:29.463
No, the way you stared at him
humiliates you.

44:29.662 --> 44:31.423
Enough. That's enough.

44:41.006 --> 44:43.234
Proud of yourself?

45:02.361 --> 45:03.272
Annie!

45:05.364 --> 45:07.943
Annie! Annie, please.

45:08.043 --> 45:11.287
- Just wait one second.
- What? What?

45:11.387 --> 45:13.965
- What are you doing here?
- I thought you knew.

45:15.608 --> 45:19.930
That you were here in Barcelona?
That you were coming to dinner?

45:20.629 --> 45:23.019
I'm sorry.

45:24.283 --> 45:27.537
It's easy to say now, isn't it, James?

45:30.723 --> 45:33.526
Just tell Felix if he still wants to
give me the information that he got,

45:33.626 --> 45:37.622
I'll be at 93 Calle Hercules,
apartment 4D.

47:54.175 --> 47:56.336
- You moved back to London?
- Yeah.

47:56.635 --> 48:00.132
But I had been in DRC,
where I spent the past year,

48:00.531 --> 48:03.468
helping out, following your lead.

48:07.011 --> 48:08.885
Don't.

48:10.398 --> 48:13.353
You come here and you want
to talk about eight years ago.

48:15.327 --> 48:18.817
Really, Jim, what did you think
was gonna happen?

48:18.958 --> 48:20.267
You coming here?

48:20.367 --> 48:23.085
I came back here 'cause somebody's
trying to kill me, and it's got to do

48:23.185 --> 48:25.490
with what happened that made me
have to leave in the first place.

48:25.789 --> 48:27.367
And what was that, Jim?

48:34.006 --> 48:35.950
Of course.

48:36.050 --> 48:38.378
You never told me
about what you did then,

48:39.077 --> 48:42.341
so why would you start now?

48:43.190 --> 48:45.802
I had to leave. I had no choice.

48:47.253 --> 48:50.223
And I don't need an explanation.
I really don't.

48:50.923 --> 48:53.359
We are different people now.

48:53.459 --> 48:55.738
I'm trying to be.

48:57.730 --> 48:59.764
What do you see in him?

49:00.464 --> 49:04.695
If a firefighter saves you from a fire,
there is a debt.

49:04.795 --> 49:07.473
Felix was there for me
when you disappeared.

49:07.573 --> 49:10.052
He did everything
he could to protect me.

49:10.251 --> 49:13.012
I've tried to pay the debt
with marriage.

49:13.112 --> 49:17.167
I'm still paying,
and he's still collecting.

49:44.735 --> 49:47.463
Felix asked me to come.

49:48.289 --> 49:50.158
He is apologetic for what happened,

49:50.457 --> 49:55.521
and he seems to think the information
he has for you is important.

49:56.722 --> 50:00.993
This is the address
of our home in the country.

50:01.952 --> 50:05.590
Join us for lunch tomorrow at 2:00?

50:08.167 --> 50:10.054
Yeah.

50:52.686 --> 50:55.185
Peek-a-boo!

51:01.487 --> 51:06.634
Romeo. Romeo. Romeo.

51:06.734 --> 51:09.210
Annie said you wanted to see me.

51:10.271 --> 51:11.464
Let's go inside.

